strated ideological rejuvenation and provided liberal thought with new emphases and visions. Arab liberals’ ongoing debates over freedom of religion, secularism, individualism, democracy and human rights were aimed at formulating of a comprehensive liberal project seeking to enact an Arab Enlightenment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLiberalismzArab countriesy20th century. 0aLiberalismzArab countriesy21st century. 0aLiberalismzIranvComparative studies. 0aLiberalismzMiddle Easty20th century. 0aLiberalismzMiddle Easty21st century. 0aLiberalismzTurkeyvComparative studies. 0aLiberalismzWestern countriesvComparative studies. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh  aArab Enlightenment.  aArab Liberalism.  aHuman Rights.  aMiddle East.  aReligion.1 aHatina, Meir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614292440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526142924423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526142924/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles